{
  "text": "On the one hand, in the production of music with acoustic instruments, gestures and sounds are intrinsically linked by the laws of physics or at least by intuitive connections that do not need any prior explanation. Beside the music they produce, every interaction is visible. Thereby the expressive intentions, as well as the intensity of emotions, are particularly vivid and underline the role of a multimodal integration [CITATION_1] . Along this line, the degree of perceived control, influenced by the additional information usually extracted from the musician's interactions, participates in the emergence of the liveness of the performance.",
